Students






















Trust Company






Location - St. Louis, Mo.


What we do
The Trust Company provides the knowledge and experience of a large, national trust company with the relationship and service of our local branch network. We work alongside the Financial Advisor to assist clients in their financial matters. These include discretionary investment management and professional administration of trust terms as well as consolidation of income, expenses and tax reporting. Our teams of trust and investment specialists provide a depth and breadth of experience to meet even the most complex trust needs.
Departments include:

Business Development
Trust Administration
Estate Settlement
Trust Investments
Trust Operations
Insurance Solutions
Real Estate
Tax
Compliance and Legal

Where we are headed
Our efforts directly support the goals of increasing both assets under care and Clients Deeply Served by improving the resources and capabilities of our branch teams to deliver Trust solutions.
What we need
Many of our Trust Company team members are experts within their field and hold advanced degrees. Specialty areas include law, finance, tax, financial planning, real estate and business. Common certifications include JD, CPA, CFA, CFP, CTFA and CLU. 
Roles within the department include:

Trust Officer
Trust Specialist
Portfolio Manager
Business Development Consultant
Insurance Specialist
Real Estate Specialist
Accountant/Tax Specialist
Attorney/Fiduciary Office
Compliance Specialist












